<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/666e548d38046cf6ec01226beeb5cb43.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 12 and A = 25 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>25.7</li><li>28.4</li><li>65.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}=\frac{{12}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{12}}{{\tan{{\left({25}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{25.734083046115}\approx{25.7}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={12}^{{2}}+{25.734083046115}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={144}+{662.24303022433}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={806.24303022433}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{806.24303022433}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{28.39441899783}\approx{28.4}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{25}^{\circ}\approx{65}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

